    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="939"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d939">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 (Potsdam)/7–3145</note>
                <head>No. 939<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Proposal by the Soviet Delegation</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d939fn1">A post–Conference letter from <persName
                            corresp="#p_PJR1">Parten</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_DBGWHJ1"
                            >Brigadier General W. H. Draper, Jr.</persName>, states: “The second
                        [definition] was presented by Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MVM1"
                            >Molotov</persName> on July 27. While both these definitions, and
                        particularly the one presented by Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MIM1"
                            >Maisky</persName> [<ref target="#d904">document No. 904</ref>], were a
                        subject of discussion, no formal action was taken on them.” (<persName
                            corresp="#p_PEW1">Pauley</persName> Files.)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation?]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-27">July 27,
                            1945</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Second Definition—War Trophies</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Under the “war trophies” is understood: <list>
                        <label>1).</label>
                        <item>All military property of Germany, including all military property,
                            which belong, is being used or was intended to be used by the military
                            and para military units of the enemy or by the members of these
                            units.</item>
                        <label>2).</label>
                        <item>Property which was used by the enemy for military purposes and which
                            in the course of the <gloss target="#t_War1">war</gloss> was removed
                            from Germany to serve the military needs of the Allies.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
